Length and width: 406 km x 2104 km

South Sudan is the number 1 in crude oil reserves in Africa.

South Sudan pumps over 155.000 barrels daily of crude oil from six fields.

They don't have their own refineries so the export to neighboring countries is about 45% through Port Sudan, because of the well-developed infrastructure.

They have one major airport, Juba International.

Their transport systems are fully owned by the Government.

Surface transportation within counties depends on unimproved roads.

The main carrier is South Sudan Railways. The railways was improved after a donation of 3.000 km of light rail from the Chinese in 2009.

South Sudan, with their two unexplored rivers can take advantage of hydroelectricity.

Hydropower is mostly used for Self-Generation in Industries.

Overall, the energy demand is about 2,5 million Kwh/day, while the electricity production is only 17,5 million Kwh/year.

Present country needs more renewable energy sources. Demand significance is not optional but a necessity.
